Here is the full Java code for a button that can be used to print "Hello World" when clicked:
```
import javax.swing.*;

public class HelloWorldButton extends JFrame {
    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

    public HelloWorldButton() {
        super("Hello World Button");
        setLayout(new BorderLayout());

        // Create the button
        JButton button = new JButton("Click me!");
        add(button, BorderLayout.CENTER);

        // Add an action listener to the button
        button.addActionListener(new ActionListener() {
            public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
                System.out.println("Hello World");
            }
        });
    }
}
```
This code creates a `JFrame` with a single button in the center. When the button is clicked, it prints "Hello World" to the console using the `System.out.println()` method.
